Package de.rwth.swc.coffee4j.junit.provider.configuration.algorithm

Interface CharacterizationAlgorithmFactoryProvider

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ExtensionContextBasedProvider<FaultCharacterizationAlgorithmFactory>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConstructorBasedProvider
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
    @FunctionalInterface
public interface CharacterizationAlgorithmFactoryProvider
extends ExtensionContextBasedProvider<FaultCharacterizationAlgorithmFactory>
    An CharacterizationAlgorithmFactoryProvider is responsible for providing exactly oneFaultCharacterizationAlgorithmFactory for use in a CombinatorialTest.

    To register a CharacterizationAlgorithmFactoryProvider, use the CharacterizationAlgorithmFactorySource annotation as demonstrated by CharacterizationAlgorithm.

    Implementations must provide a no-args constructor.

    This is more or less a copy of ArgumentsProvider from the junit-jupiter-params project.
